thread.title: The ‘Tina Fey Factor’ Boosts Broadway Ticket Sales

author: Charles Passy
title: The ‘Tina Fey Factor’ Boosts Broadway Ticket Sales
text:
It’s mean season on Broadway.
“Mean Girls,” the musical based on the 2004 movie of the same name, has drawn capacity crowds and grossed nearly $2.6 million during the first two weeks of previews before its official opening on April 8, according to trade group Broadway League.
